&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Crisis and Emergency&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Nurses – Mental Health&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Band 5 £24,907 - £30,615 pa pro rata (dependent on experience)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Woodland View Nursing Home, Norton, Sheffield S8 8BG &amp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Birch Avenue Nursing Home, 67 Birch Avenue Chapeltown, S35 1RQ&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5 (Part time positions also available)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post Ref: 457-20-106-QN&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Registered Nurse who enjoys leading and delivering person centred care? Here is an opportunity to be part of something special and make a difference in many people’s lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Woodland View and Birch Avenue Nursing homes are services for people with advanced and complex dementia and we are seeking compassionate and ambitious nurses to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be a Registered Nurse Mental Health or Adult (RNMH / RGN), with a keen interest in working with people with dementia. Successful applicant will be able to lead a team of staff in a person centred way, be motivated and able to demonstrate a positive attitude to working with dementia in crisis. You will need to be flexible in your approach to shift working, possess effective communication skills and have the ability to work in a multi-professional team and also under your own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please ensure you read the post’s job description and person specification and that your supporting information reflects this as your application will be judged against these criteria.&lt;/p&gt;
